These are Puzzles for 2x5 Level 4

.:: Puzzle 2x5-Level-4-1::.
There are 5 different nationalities: egyptian, thai, british, chinese, japanese
City: venice, new-york, miami, prague, liverpool
1. the person traveling to prague is in an odd position##4
2. the person traveling to prague is in the middle##1
3. the japanese is on the left or right of the person traveling to venice##3
4. the british is on the right of the chinese##1
5. the egyptian is between the person traveling to prague and the person traveling to miami##2
6. the japanese is in the middle##1
7. the person traveling to prague is on the right of the person traveling to liverpool##1
8. the chinese is on the left or right of the japanese##3

.:: Answer ::.
|               |   1    |      2      |   3    |    4    |    5    |
| Nationality          | thai | egyptian | japanese | chinese | british |
| City   | miami  | liverpool      | prague   | venice     | new-york    |

 #################################

 
.:: Puzzle 2x5-Level-4-2::.
5 different brands of cigars are smoked: pall-mall, havana, tiparillo, oliveros, ritmeester
There are 5 different nationalities: canadian, japanese, pakistani, turkish, mexican
1. the pall-mall-smoker is in an even position##4
2. the pall-mall-smoker is on the right of the turkish##1
3. the ritmeester-smoker is in the middle##1
4. the mexican is on the left or right of the ritmeester-smoker##3
5. the canadian is between the tiparillo-smoker and the turkish##2
6. the pakistani is on the right of the pall-mall-smoker##1
7. the tiparillo-smoker is on the left of the oliveros-smoker##1

.:: Answer ::.
|            |      1       |     2     |    3     |      4      |    5    |
| Cigar   | tiparillo     | oliveros       | ritmeester    | pall-mall | havana   |
| Nationality      | japanese | canadian | turkish | mexican      | pakistani |

 #################################

 
.:: Puzzle 2x5-Level-4-3::.
The people's birthday is in 5 different months: may, january, november, september, october
5 different games are played: chess, mah-jongg, canasta, billiard, whist
1. the person playing billiard is the person who's birthday is in may##1
2. the person playing mah-jongg is in an even position##4
3. the person playing mah-jongg is on the right of the person playing canasta##1
4. the person who's birthday is in january is on the left or right of the person playing chess##3
5. the person playing canasta is on the left or right of the person playing chess##3
6. the person playing whist is on the left or right of the person playing mah-jongg##3
7. the person who's birthday is in november is on the right of the person who's birthday is in may##1
8. the person who's birthday is in october is on the far left or far right##3

.:: Answer ::.
|               |     1      |      2       |     3      |     4      |      5      |
| Birthday         | may | november | january | september    | october |
| Game   | billiard     | chess        | canasta      | mah-jongg | whist      |

 #################################

 
.:: Puzzle 2x5-Level-4-4::.
The people prefer 5 different music-genres: rock, blues, folk, jazz, metal
The people have 5 different jobs:  mechanic, architect, dancer, scientist, electrician
1. the fan of folk is in the middle##1
2. the mechanic is in an even position##4
3. the architect is on the far right##1
4. the fan of metal is the architect##1
5. the fan of folk is on the right of the electrician##1
6. the fan of blues is between the dancer and the fan of metal##2
7. the electrician is the fan of jazz##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |     1      |   2    |       3       |     4     |      5       |
| Music-Genre         | rock      | jazz | folk | blues   | metal  |
| Job   | scientist | electrician    | dancer        | mechanic | architect |

 #################################

 
.:: Puzzle 2x5-Level-4-5::.
5 different games are played: chess, bridge, whist, monopoly, domino
House: victorian, modern, palace, tower, gothic-revival
1. the person playing chess is in an odd position##4
2. the person playing bridge is on the left of the victorian house##1
3. the person playing monopoly is on the left of the gothic-revival house##1
4. the palace house is on the left or right of the person playing bridge##3
5. the gothic-revival house is on the far right##1
6. the person playing chess is on the right of the tower house##1
7. the modern house is in an even position##4
8. the person playing whist is on the far right##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |    1     |    2     |     3      |     4     |    5     |
| Game      | domino      | bridge | chess   | monopoly  | whist  |
| House   | palace | tower | victorian | modern | gothic-revival |

