.:: Puzzle 2x5-Level-4-6::.
City: new-york, berlin, paris, liverpool, london
The people use 5 different means of transport: trike, train, airplane, scooter, skateboard
1. the person traveling to berlin is on the far left##1
2. the person driving the train is between the person driving the skateboard and the person traveling to paris##2
3. the person traveling to liverpool is on the right of the person traveling to new-york##1
4. the person traveling to paris is on the right of the person driving the train##1
5. the person driving the airplane is the person traveling to paris##1
6. the person driving the airplane is in an even position##4
7. the person traveling to liverpool is on the left or right of the person traveling to new-york##3
8. the person driving the scooter is on the right of the person traveling to paris##1

.:: Answer ::.
|            |      1      |         2          |    3     |     4     |       5        |
| City   | berlin        | new-york                | liverpool  | paris  | london            |
| Transport        | trike | skateboard | train | airplane | scooter |

